t=British Comedy|last=Guide|website=British Comedy Guide}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''Horrible Histories Special: Crooked King John and Magna Carta''\n| Kidscreen Award for Best Non-Animated or Mixed Series\n| {{Won}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kidscreen.com/2016/02/09/the-2016-kidscreen-awards-winners-are/|title=The 2016 Kidscreen Awards winners are\u2026|publisher=}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''Horrible Histories Special: Awesome Alfred the Great''\n| Broadcast Award for Best Children's Programme\n| {{Nominated}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://broadcastawards.co.uk/shortlist/|title=shortlist|publisher=}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Horrible Histories Special: Crooked King John and Magna Carta''\n| BAFTA Children's Award for Best Comedy\n| {{Nominated}}<ref name=\"2015 BACA\" />\n|-\n| 2015\n| '' Jessica Ransom'' as Mary, Queen of Scots\n| BAFTA Children's Award for Best Performer\n| {{Won}}<ref name=\"2015 BACA\" />\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Horrible Histories Special: Crooked King John and Magna Carta''\n| BAFTA Children's Award for Best Writing\n| {{Nominated}}<ref name=\"2015 BACA\">{{cite web | url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2015/childrens | title=Children's Awards 2015| publisher=BAFTA | date=22 October 2015 | accessdate=12 September 2016}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==DVD and online releases==\nThe series, treated as the sixth of the [[Horrible Histories (2009 TV series)|original 2009\u20132013 run]], was released on [[DVD region code#2|Region 2]] DVD on 31 August 2015. Episodes are also available online through UK [[iTunes]] as \"Series 6: Rotten Rulers\". The 2016 specials were released on DVD under \"The Specials II\" on 12 September 2016. The seventh series, including its then-unaired episodes, was released on DVD on 6 November 2017 for regions 2 and 4.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{BBC programme}}\n* {{British Comedy Guide|tv|horrible_histories|Horrible Histories}}\n* [http://www.bafta.org/whats-on/bafta-kids-tv-preview-horrible-histories-special-staggering-storytellers Q&A with cast and crew of 2015 revival]\n* {{IMDb title|1400819}}\n\n{{Horrible Histories}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:2010s British children's television series]]\n[[Category:BBC children's television programmes]]\n[[Category:BBC television comedy]]\n[[Category:BBC television sketch shows]]\n[[Category:Children's comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Horrible Histories]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on children's books]]\n[[Category:British television programmes featuring puppetry]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:British television sketch shows]]\n[[Category:Depictions of Julius Caesar on television]]\n", "name_user": "Kahtar", "label": "safe", "comment": "Repair CS1 error(s), replaced: website=www. \u2192 website=", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horrible_Histories_(2015_TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "The Dinner (2013 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2013 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Dinner\n| image          = The Dinner 2013 poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Menno Meyjes]]\n| producer       = [[Hans de Weers]] \n| writer         = Menno Meyjes\n| based on       = {{Based on|''[[Het diner]]''|[[Herman Koch]]}}}\n| starring       = [[Thekla Reuten]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Sander Snoep\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2013|9|9|TIFF|2013|11|7|Netherlands|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 88 minutes\n| country        = Netherlands\n| language       = Dutch\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''The Dinner''''' ({{lang-nl|'''Het Diner'''}}) is a 2013 Dutch [[drama film]] written and directed by [[Menno Meyjes]]. It was screened in the Contemporary World Cinema section at the [[2013 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"TIFF\">{{cite web |url=http://tiff.net/filmsandschedules/festival/2013/dinner |title=The Dinner |accessdate=20 August 2013 |work=TIFF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130831075929/http://tiff.net/filmsandschedules/festival/2013/dinner |archivedate=31 August 2013  }}</ref><ref name=\"Indiewire\">{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/toronto-adds-75-titles-to-2013-edition-james-franco-alex-gibney-hayao-miyazaki-sean-durkin-and-kevin-macdonald-among-them?page=2 |title=Toronto Adds 75+ Titles To 2013 Edition |accessdate=20 August 2013 |work=Indiewire}}</ref> The film is based on [[Herman Koch]]'s novel ''[[Het diner]]''.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Thekla Reuten]] as Claire\n* [[Kim van Kooten]] as Babette\n* [[Daan Schuurmans]] as Serge\n* [[Jacob Derwig]] as Paul\n* [[Sabine Soetanto]]\n* [[Reinout Bussemaker]] as Rector\n* [[Gusta Geleynse]] as Dakloze\n* [[Wil van der Meer]] as Tonio\n* [[Jonas Smulders]] as Michel\n* [[Harpert Michielsen]] as Gerant\n* [[Andre Dongelmans]] as Beau\n* [[Serge Mensink]] as Rick\n\n== See also ==\n*''[[The Dinner (2014 film)|The Dinner]]'' (2014)\n*''[[The Dinner (2017 film)|The Dinner]]'' (2017)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2352230|The Dinner}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dinner}}\n[[Category:2013 films]]\n[[Category:2013 drama films]]\n[[Category:Dutch films]]\n[[Category:Dutch drama films]]\n[[Category:Dutch-language films]]\n{{Netherlands-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2013 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Dinner\n| image          = The Dinner 2013 poster.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Menno Meyjes]]\n| producer       = [[Hans de Weers]] \n| writer         = Menno Meyjes\n| based on       = {{Based on|''[[Het diner]]''|[[Herman Koch]]}}}\n| starring       = [[Thekla Reuten]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Sander Snoep\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|2013|9|9|TIFF|2013|11|7|Netherlands|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 88 minutes\n| country        = Netherlands\n| language       = Dutch\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''The Dinner''''' ({{lang-nl|'''Het Diner'''}}) is a 2013 Dutch [[drama film]] written and directed by [[Menno Meyjes]]. It was screened in the Contemporary World Cinema section at the [[2013 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"TIFF\">{{cite web |url=http://tiff.net/filmsandschedules/festival/2013/dinner |title=The Dinner |accessdate=20 August 2013 |work=TIFF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130831075929/http://tiff.net/filmsandschedules/festival/2013/dinner |archivedate=31 August 2013  }}</ref><ref name=\"Indiewire\">{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/toronto-adds-75-titles-to-2013-edition-james-franco-alex-gibney-hayao-miyazaki-sean-durkin-and-kevin-macdonald-among-them?page=2 |title=Toronto Adds 75+ Titles To 2013 Edition |acces